stepAnswer: You should label all of your data points, by default, and only remove those that must be removed.
stepBody: Which of the following is not true?
choices: The title on a page or chart can help your audience remember your data.
You should label as few data points as you can get away with, given your task, your audience, and your goals.
You should label all of your data points, by default, and only remove those that must be removed.
